p align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: way to go USA..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;Zephyris: I haven't seen a single apathetic person post in this thread. What the hell are you talking about? Being against the death penalty is quite the opposite of being apathetic. Those like me that have spoken against it, care very much about right and wrong. I don't think it is right to kill someone simply because they are a killer. That's not justice, it's simply revenge.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Raedwulf, you'll notice that my post began with the three words &quot; If a Person&quot;.  It was meant to be an educational post directed at those who would say Mcveigh shouldn't be executed.  If a person believes we should have let him live, then they are being apathetic to the general moral beliefs that we share as a society of what is right and what is wrong.<br>
<br>
Apathy is not caring one way or another or not having the desire to take a stand for something.  In the case of these people, they dont care what is right, but instead want their personal opinions enforced.  <br>
<br>
Looking back at my post, I should have included some statement referring to those against executing him but at the time of the post, I made an error. I'm human, that tends to happen from time to time you know.<br>
<br>
Lastly, the things I pointed out at the end of my post go hand in hand with the bleeding heart liberal mentality which I cannot stand.  If you are offended by my comparisons/examples then pick an uncharted island and I'll lobby like hell to get you some death row neighbors.  I promise you that.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraedwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raedwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/12/01 12:01:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: way to go USA..</span><hr size=1> Zeph:  You are doing more harm than good to your arguments.  You can keep claiming what you mean by the &quot;apathy&quot;, but you'd be wrong.  I can create my own definition for all sorts of words, but if it's not the definition anyone else uses, I might as well be typing in random letters on the keyboard.  Your use of the word &quot;apathy&quot; is akin to my claiming that when I say &quot;red&quot;, I really mean &quot;intelligent.&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm afraid that you are mistaken on quite a number of things.  &quot;they dont care what is right, but instead want their personal opinions enforced.&quot;  Isn't that the same as you?  Just because you are in the majority in the US, does this mean your position is right?  In 1776, the majority felt that slavery was right.  Were they correct?  Of course not.<br>
<br>
&quot;bleeding heart liberal mentality.&quot;  I'm sorry that you still don't get it.  I'm neither a &quot;bleeding heart&quot; nor a &quot;liberal,&quot; yet I'm against the death penalty.  Disagreeing with the majority is not being apathetic.  Your &quot;if a person&quot; intro is meaningless regarding your use of the term &quot;apathetic.&quot;  And as a number of those who have spoken out against the execution were family members of victims, your premise is contraindicated by the very matters you cite.<br>
<br>
If anyone disagrees with you, then they should be sent somewhere else?  I think you'll find yourself alone in a hurry.  Although many might agree with you on this point, there are bound to be other issues you won't agree with them on.  Even if you were a complete Tableau Raza (spelling?) and chose the &quot;majority&quot; opinion on every subject, you'd soon find yourself alone again, for everyone has views on some issue or another that aren't popular.  A few of the ones you've mentioned in this post would seem to put you in the minority.<br>
<br>
Again, I'm not suggesting that people convicted of &quot;capital crimes&quot; ought to be let out.  I think they ought to be locked up forever, or until we demonstrate that in fact, they weren't guilty.  We can't do that after an execution, can we?<br>
<br>
Just as a bit of a funny point:  Please let us know how to &quot;pick&quot; an uncharted island.  If it is uncharted (meaning unknown), how is anyone to pick it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessage?topicID=2045.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessage?topicID=2031.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.emailToFriend?topicID=2006.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.threadControl?topicID=2006.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2006.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2006.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub4.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="emarrmessageboardrules">Message Board Rules<option value="emarrlinks">Links<option value="emarrupcomingmmorpgs">Upcoming MMOG's<option value="emarrfrm16">The Emarr Quadrant<option value="emarrgeneral">General<option value="emarrfrm17">Funny Stuff<option value="emarrbazaar">Item Bazaar<option value="emarrscrolls